Chunk 7: Power Analysis

7.1) load the pwr library 7.2) Start with Hemoglobin data: create a proportional table of obervations in different populations vs.elevations 7.3) Calculate the power for each of the four countries, given the proportions of observations and sample sizes for each country and a significance level of 0.05. Which countries have the highest power? Why do you think this is the case? 7.4) What happens when you decrease the expected significance level to 0.01. Interpret these results. 7.5) What happens when you decrease half the number of observations collected in each population but retain a significance level of 0.5. Interpret these results. 7.6) Even when power is > 0.8, why might this study be flawed?
